===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{liushu|p}}.

The oracle bone script form consisted of two strings with [[cowry|cowries]] attached. Some forms of the oracle bone script contained an additional {{zh-l|*人}} which later evolved into {{och-l|勹}}, which served as a phonetic component. The glyph was eventually corrupted to a {{zh-etym-double|月|moon|nocap=y}}.

''{{w|Shuowen}}'' erroneously suggests {{och-l|朋}} was the ancient form of {{och-l|鳳}}.

